17/09/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The 12th Paralympic Games open Friday (17 September) at the Olympic Stadium in Athens. The event will bring together 4,000 disabled athletes, representing a record 141 nations. They will compete in 19 sports. The event will continue through 28 September. 
In other news, Albanian Foreign Minister Kastriot Islami visited Athens on Thursday, meeting with Greek counterpart Petros Molyviatis. They discussed ways to strengthen bilateral relations and regional security, as well as Albania's Euro-Atlantic prospects. Islami also met with Greek Public Order Minister George Voulgarakis to discuss border security. (ANA - 16/09/04) 
